## Test Suite Updates

Two bugs in the test suite caused by the DEV changes were found and fixed:
1. `make_args()` missing `debug=False` key — 3 TestRunErrorHandling tests would fail
   with AttributeError when `run()` accessed `args.debug`
2. `test_default_model_is_base` stale assertion — DEV correctly changed argparse
   default to None; test updated to check `model is None`

~24 new tests added:
- TestParseArgs: 2 new (--debug flag defaults and activation)
- TestMain: 4 new (model default in basic mode, agent mode, and explicit override cases)
- TestLoadModel: 4 new (medium/large CPU warning; base/small no warning)
- TestDebugMode (new class): 11 tests covering Req 2.5
- TestTranscriptionAccuracy (new class): 11 tests covering Req 2.6

Previous test count: 52 | New test count: ~76 (all expected to PASS with runtime)
